cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper deals with image registration using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of an artificial agent for learning an optimal registration strategy also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a greedy supervised approach for training the agent, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the use of attention-driven hierarchical strategy for coping with the dimensionality of the problem is related to robotics and control (cs.RO).
